      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Image Optimization?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Image optimization is the process of reducing image file size without compromising quality to improve website loading speed and performance."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Image Optimization Matters"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Images often make up the largest portion of a webpage. Optimizing them reduces load time, improves user experience, and boosts SEO rankings."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Modern Image Formats"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Format", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["JPEG", "Good for photos"],
          ["PNG", "Supports transparency"],
          ["WebP", "Better compression and quality"],
          ["AVIF", "Next-gen format with high compression"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"image.webp\" alt=\"Optimized Image\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Responsive Images"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Serve different image sizes based on screen resolution using srcset."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"small.jpg\"\n     srcset=\"medium.jpg 768w, large.jpg 1200w\"\n     alt=\"Responsive Image\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Lazy Loading Images"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<img src=\"image.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Lazy Image\">"
    },
    {
